    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Her Majesty’s Treasury</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Laird Brothers</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury
                                        Chambers,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 2, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen:</hi> In reply to your further letter
                                of 25th ultimo, I am desired by the lords commissioners of her
                                Majesty’s treasury to acquaint you that her Majesty’s government
                                cannot permit the iron-clad vessels built in your yard, and now
                                under seizure, to be completed.</p>
                <p>I am, gentlemen, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. A. HAMILTON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Messrs. <hi rend="smallcaps">Laird Brothers,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Birkenhead Iron Works, Birkenhead.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
